About 60 pupils were rushed to hospital after complaining of stomach cramps and vomiting after eating sweets distributed by an unknown man. JOHANNESBURG - Gauteng Education MEC Panyaza Lesufi has confirmed preliminary results show that sweets handed out to pupils at the Suidheuwels Primary School and two other schools were laced with drugs.About 60 pupils were rushed to hospital on Wednesday after complaining of stomach cramps and vomiting. Two of them were admitted in a critical condition. It's understood an unknown man has been distributing the sweets to pupils in the south of Johannesburg. Lesufi says police are working with pupils and the public to put identity kit together. I m hopeful because police have given us people who will assist us in case we identified the suspect. (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)